# Import Path Configuration

## Absolute Imports

The project is configured to use absolute imports for the `pages` and `tests` directories as defined in [tsconfig.json](mdc:evaluate_stagehand/tsconfig.json):

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "pages/*": [
        "pages/*"
      ],
      "tests/*": [
        "tests/*"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

## How to Import

### Preferred (Absolute Import)

Use imports starting with the mapped path:

```typescript
// Preferred way - absolute imports
import { HomePage } from "pages/landing-page.js";
import { LoginPage } from "pages/recruiter/login-page/recruiter-login-page.js";
import { SomeTest } from "tests/recruiter/assessment/some-test.js";
```

### Avoid (Relative Import)

Don't use relative paths with multiple levels:

```typescript
// Avoid this - relative imports with ../../../
import { HomePage } from "../../../pages/landing-page.js";
```

## Benefits

- Cleaner imports without ../../../ notation
- Easier to move files without breaking imports
- Improved code readability
- Better IDE support for imports
